#: ../../source/administration/downgrade.rst:13
msgid "Existing install directory - *{install-path}*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/downgrade.rst:14
msgid ""
"If you don't know where Mattermost Server is installed, use the ``whereis"
" mattermost`` command. The output should be similar to "
"*/opt/mattermost/bin/mattermost*. The install directory is everything "
"before the last occurrence of the string */mattermost*. In this example, "
"the *{install-path}* is ``/opt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/downgrade.rst:15
msgid "Location of your local storage directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/downgrade.rst:16
msgid ""
"The local storage directory contains all the files that users have "
"attached to their messages. If you don't know its location, open the "
"System Console and go to **Files > Storage** and read the value in "
"**Local Storage Directory**. Relative paths are relative to the "
"``mattermost`` directory. For example, if the local storage directory is "
"``./data/`` then the absolute path is ``{install-path}/mattermost/data``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/downgrade.rst:18
msgid "Owner and group of the install directory - *{owner}* and *{group}*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/downgrade.rst:18
msgid ""
"Use the ``ls -l {install-path}/mattermost/bin/mattermost`` command to get"
" the owner and group."
msgstr ""

